SIMPLE: speckle
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Speckle
<hw>Spec"kle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Dim. of
<ets>speck</ets>; cf. D. <ets>spikkel</ets>.]</ety> <def>A little or
spot in or anything, of a different substance or color from that of the
thing itself.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An huge great serpent, all with <qex>speckles</qex> pied.</q>
<rj><qau>Spebser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Speckle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Speckle
<hw>Spec"kle</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Speckled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Speckling</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <def>To mark with small
spots of a different color from that of the rest of the surface; to
variegate with spots of a different color from the ground or
surface.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Speckled</ent>⟦br⟧
